<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-07-03T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-07-03T05:00:00-05:00" n="246" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d246">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/539: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-07-03T12:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">July 3,
                                        1923—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 12:30
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>111. Your 38, June 27, 2 [<hi rend="italic">1</hi>] p.m. I am informed
                            Government contemplates transfer to Greece of refugees in question after
                            signing of peace.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>